Vodacom Tanzania Names Airtel Kenya’s Meza as Managing Director

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-09-05T14:24:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/vodacom-tanzania-names-airtel-kenya-s-ceo-rene-meza-as-managing-director.html
Vodacom Group Ltd. (VOD) ’s Tanzanian unit
hired Rene Meza, the former chief executive officer of rival
 Bharti Airtel Ltd. (BHARTI) ’s Kenyan unit, as its managing director.  Meza replaces Dietlof Mare, who requested a change in roles
after spending five years in Tanzania, Vodacom said in an e-
mailed statement today from Johannesburg. Meza previously worked
in countries including Paraguay, Pakistan and  Kenya , and served
as CEO of Millicom International Cellular SA’s operations in
Tanzania, it said.  Airtel Kenya Ltd., Kenya’s second-biggest mobile operator,
said in a separate statement that it appointed Shivan Bhargava
as chief operating officer to oversee the company’s operations
in East Africa’s largest economy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 